UNIX Practice

1)Create directory
    mkdir data_engineering
2)Create multiple folders
    mkdir -p data_engineering/{logs,scripts,data,outputs}
3)Create 5 empty files
    touch data_engineering/logs/file{1..5}.txt
4)Copy files
    cp data_engineering/logs/* data_engineering/backup_logs/
5)Rename directory
    mv backup_logs archive_logs
6)Delete directory with files
    rm -rf archive_logs
7)Move all .txt files
    mv *.txt data_engineering/data/
8)View file
    cat orders.log
9) First 20 rows
head -n 20 orders.log
10) Last 50 rows
tail -n 50 orders.log
11) Real-time log monitoring
tail -f orders.log
12) Count lines, words, characters
wc orders.log
13) Show line numbers
cat -n orders.log
14) Find ERROR
grep "ERROR" orders.log
15) Case insensitive
grep -i "failed" orders.log
16) With line numbers
grep -n "ERROR" orders.log
17) Count errors
grep -c "ERROR" orders.log
18) Exclude SUCCESS
grep -v "SUCCESS" orders.log
19) Multiple patterns
grep -E "ERROR|FAILED" orders.log
20) Sort file
sort file.txt
21) Sort numbers
sort -n file.txt
22) Sort by 3rd column
sort -t',' -k3 file.csv
23) Descending
sort -r file.txt
24) Remove duplicates
sort file.txt | uniq
25) Count duplicates
sort file.txt | uniq -c
26) Show duplicates only
sort file.txt | uniq -d
27) Column Extraction (cut & awk)
    Extract columns
    cut -d',' -f1 orders.csv
    Multiple columns
    cut -d',' -f1,3 orders.csv
    Using awk
    awk -F',' '{print $1}' orders.csv
    Filter rows
    awk -F',' '$3 > 600' orders.csv
    Sum revenue
    awk -F',' '{sum += $3} END {print sum}' orders.csv
    Count rows
    awk 'END {print NR}' orders.csv
28) Date & Timestamp
    Current date
    date
    Current timestamp
    date +"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"
    Only year
    date +"%Y"
    Month
    date +"%m"
    Week number
    date +"%U"
    Yesterday
    date -d "yesterday"
    Tomorrow
    date -d "tomorrow"
    Format conversion
    date -d "2025-03-06" +"%d-%m-%Y"
2 days ago
    date -d "2 days ago"
    Extract hour
    date +"%H"
29) File Filtering by Time
    Modified last 1 day
    find . -mtime -1
    Last 7 days
    find . -mtime -7
    Files > 1MB
    find . -size +1M
    Created today
    find . -mtime 0
    Delete older than 30 days
    find . -mtime +30 -delete
30) Pipeline & Redirection
    Save output
    ls > files.txt
    Append output
    ls >> files.txt
    Count ERROR lines
    grep "ERROR" log.txt | wc -l
    Unique customer IDs
    cut -d',' -f1 orders.csv | sort | uniq
    Sort and save
    sort orders.csv > sorted_orders.csv
31)Compression
Compress file
gzip file.txt
Uncompress
gunzip file.txt.gz
Create tar
tar -cvf logs.tar logs/
Extract tar
tar -xvf logs.tar
Compress folder
tar -czvf logs.tar.gz logs/
32)Real Data Engineer Scenarios
Count failed jobs
grep "FAILED" jobs.log | wc -l
Extract failed job IDs
grep "FAILED" jobs.log | cut -d',' -f1
Latest job date
cut -d',' -f2 jobs.log | sort | tail -1
Unique job IDs
cut -d',' -f1 jobs.log | sort | uniq
33) Revenue Problems
Total revenue
awk -F',' '{sum += $3} END {print sum}' orders.csv
Revenue per date
awk -F',' '{arr[$2]+=$3} END {for(i in arr) print i, arr[i]}' orders.csv
Max amount
awk -F',' 'max<$3 {max=$3} END {print max}' orders.csv
Orders per day
cut -d',' -f2 orders.csv | sort | uniq -c
